issues.description: The problem statement’s UML and instructions specify that the interface method messageOnMilk() returns boolean (true if milking succeeded, false otherwise), but the solution’s Milkable interface and all implementations declare and return String. This return-type mismatch will confuse students about whether messageOnMilk should be boolean or String and will conflict with any tests relying on the specified boolean signature.
issues.suggested_fix: Either update the problem statement (UML and instructions) to specify messageOnMilk() returns String (with an appropriate message), or revise the solution’s interface and implementations so messageOnMilk() returns boolean, matching the original specification.
